<Base title="Steady — Privacy Policy" doc>
  <nav><a href="/steady/">← Steady</a></nav>
  <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
  <p class="date">Effective July 6, 2026</p>

  <h2>The short version</h2>
  <p>Steady collects nothing. Your readings, medications, and symptoms stay on your device and in services you control.</p>

  <h2>Health data</h2>
  <p>With your permission, Steady reads and writes blood pressure, blood glucose, weight, heart rate,
     and blood oxygen records in Apple Health. Notes and meal context may be saved with those records
     as Apple Health metadata. You can revoke access at any time in Settings → Health →
     Data Access &amp; Devices.</p>

  <h2>Your data</h2>
  <p>Medication schedules, dose check-offs, symptoms, and app settings are stored locally on your
     device. If iCloud sync is enabled, that data syncs through your personal iCloud account using
     Apple's CloudKit. Your data never touches our servers, because we don't have any.</p>

  <h2>What we don't do</h2>
  <p>No accounts. No analytics. No ads. No third-party SDKs. No tracking of any kind. We never
     use Health data for marketing, and we never disclose it to third parties.</p>

  <h2>Purchases</h2>
  <p>The one-time unlock is processed entirely by Apple through the App Store. We never see your
     payment details.</p>

  <h2>Changes</h2>
  <p>If this policy ever changes, the update will be posted on this page with a new effective date.</p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>Questions? Visit <a href="/steady/support/">Support</a>.</p>
</Base>
